{"TopicId":134483,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"Minmus Base Screwup","CreatedByName":"Generic","CreatedById":160375,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-18T22:01:07Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Generic","CreatedById":160375,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-18T22:01:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLanded the core module of my new Minmus Base, sent\u00A0Valentina outside, destroyed 3 of the 4 solar panels and realised i didn\u0027t bring a ladder.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKill me.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022aZK9NPP.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/aZK9NPP.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbart","CreatedById":78303,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-18T22:05:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLuckily the jetpacks have enough DV to get you into freakin\u0027 ORBIT on Minmus. Reaching the door of the lander shouldn\u0027t be that big of a deal \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Generic","CreatedById":160375,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-18T22:09:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222463301\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022134483\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221458338751\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002278303\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kerbart\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, Kerbart said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLuckily the jetpacks have enough DV to get you into freakin\u0027 ORBIT on Minmus. Reaching the door of the lander shouldn\u0027t be that big of a deal \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut ladders are more realistic \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u00A0it feels more authentic.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Snark","CreatedById":125662,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-18T22:48:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222463308\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022134483\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221458338955\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022160375\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Generic\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n41 minutes ago, Generic said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut ladders are more realistic \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u00A0it feels more authentic.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, okay then, don\u0027t go to orbit if it feels overpowered (I kinda agree with you, there).\u00A0 But seriously, the gravity on Minmus is so low that it doesn\u0027t seem unreasonable that you can fly there.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you don\u0027t want to use an EVA pack, just \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cu\u003Ejump\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/em\u003E; a kerbal jumping on Minmus can easily go higher than that lander.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe silhouette is so dark that it\u0027s hard for me to tell, but is that big cylindrical part on the bottom a hitchhiker module?\u00A0 If that\u0027s the case, just retract the landing gear so you settle down on the surface, then Val can just walk up to the lander and climb into the hatch.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr retract the landing gear, use the reaction torque from the cupola to tip your whole craft over and bring the cupola hatch down within easy reach of Val.\u00A0 Then board, and use the torque to turn right-side-up again.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere.\u00A0 There\u0027s four different solutions to the problem, any one of which would work.\u00A0 Will that do?\u00A0 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Fearless Son","CreatedById":133397,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-18T22:58:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd if even jetpacks and jumping feels too inauthentic for you, then try and get up there by scrambling. \u00A0Go up to a landing leg and let Val indulge her \u003Cem\u003EAssassin\u0027s Creed\u003C/em\u003E fantasy in the low gravity by scaling the side of the base module. \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"seaces","CreatedById":131939,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-18T23:20:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSince this is a core I suspect you will send more modules? If so before doing it check for mods KIS and KAS those will allow your engineer to fix, replace and put new parts on EVA. So when you send next module you could send one engineer with spare parts. Plus those mods will help with base buildings etc.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Xavven","CreatedById":100398,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-18T23:33:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222463308\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022134483\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221458338955\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022160375\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Generic\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Generic said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut ladders are more realistic \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u00A0it feels more authentic.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI agree with you. It feels inauthentic to have a lander or base with a high hatch that doesn\u0027t have a ladder. However, if you were Valentina, what would you do? Think \u0022The Martian\u0022 or Apollo 13. Improvise and adapt to make it home.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-03-18T23:34:10Z\u0022 title=\u002203/18/2016 11:34  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 18, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Xavven\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Wallygator","CreatedById":97357,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-18T23:37:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLooks like a HH can on the bottom with an accessible\u00A0hatch. So as mentioned above, retract\u00A0the gear,\u00A0get in, extend gear, have snack.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-03-18T23:38:47Z\u0022 title=\u002203/18/2016 11:38  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 18, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Wallygator\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Atlas2342","CreatedById":155194,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-18T23:59:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI dont think moving the lander itself is an option. Remember she\u00A0is outside on EVA...Maybe just jump, climb up the ladder, etc. like what the others suggested...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Generic","CreatedById":160375,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-19T00:09:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for all the replies \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI fixed the solar panels with KIS like \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/131939-seaces/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022131939\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/131939-seaces/\u0022\u003E@seaces\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0said and i\u0027m using the jetpack to return.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/125662-snark/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022125662\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/125662-snark/\u0022\u003E@Snark\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0Yes, it\u0027s a\u00A0H\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003Eitchhiker module.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022eGIxdGK.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/eGIxdGK.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-03-19T01:07:11Z\u0022 title=\u002203/19/2016 01:07  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 19, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Generic\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbart","CreatedById":78303,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-19T04:44:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can pretend they form a \u003Cs\u003Ehuman\u003C/s\u003E \u00A0kerbal\u00A0chain to hoist the bottom one into the station.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLADIES AND GENTLEMEN! THE KERMAN BROTHERS ARE GOING TO PERFORM A\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EDANGEROUS STUNT\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0NEVER PERFORMED BEFORE!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-03-19T04:45:03Z\u0022 title=\u002203/19/2016 04:45  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 19, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Kerbart\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"samstarman5","CreatedById":12469,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-19T04:47:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222463406\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022134483\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221458343219\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022131939\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022seaces\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, seaces said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSince this is a core I suspect you will send more modules? If so before doing it check for mods KIS and KAS those will allow your engineer to fix, replace and put new parts on EVA. So when you send next module you could send one engineer with spare parts. Plus those mods will help with base buildings etc.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSpeaking of being unrealistic. Pretty sure Apollo 13 didn\u0027t have such luxuries except what they could cannibalize.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"pandaman","CreatedById":130621,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-19T12:27:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhilst I get the OPs point about it \u0027not feeling right\u0027 not using a ladder, I don\u0027t see what\u0027s unrealistic about the low gravity on any astronomical body (Minmus in this case) allowing a guy or gal\u00A0with a suitably powerful jet pack to \u0027fly\u0027. \u00A0It\u0027s no different in principle to a rocket being able to lift off from KSC.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Frank_G","CreatedById":100000,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-19T12:41:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe all did those kinda mis...sions... \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWelcome to the club and keep on going!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FancyMouse","CreatedById":142946,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-19T13:16:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222463942\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022134483\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221458390426\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022130621\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022pandaman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n48 minutes ago, pandaman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhilst I get the OPs point about it \u0027not feeling right\u0027 not using a ladder, I don\u0027t see what\u0027s unrealistic about the low gravity on any astronomical body (Minmus in this case) allowing a guy or gal\u00A0with a suitably powerful jet pack to \u0027fly\u0027. \u00A0It\u0027s no different in principle to a rocket being able to lift off from KSC.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf EVA monoprop cannot be refilled for free...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"pandaman","CreatedById":130621,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-19T13:51:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222463970\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022134483\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221458393379\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022142946\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022FancyMouse\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n30 minutes ago, FancyMouse said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf EVA monoprop cannot be refilled for free...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAgreed, that is a bit unrealistic, but you still have to be able to get to a capsule to refill it. \u00A0No matter how much fuel you carry if you run out of gas before \u00A0you get to the gas station you still aren\u0027t going to get there under your own steam.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}